<div type="apparatus">
<head>Apparatus</head>
<p>b. l. 1, or <foreign lang="grc"><supplied reason="lost">Σεβ</supplied>άστω<supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied></foreign></p>
</div>
<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>b: <gap dim="left" extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/> for Augustus <gap dim="right" extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/> <note place="not specified" anchored="yes">or</note> <gap dim="left" extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/> of Augusti <gap dim="right" extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/></p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>The reference is probably to the emperor Hadrian. The verb in b might describe a function of a responsible official/donor, such as <foreign lang="grc"><supplied reason="lost">ἀρχιερα</supplied>τευοντ<gap dim="right" reason="lost"/></foreign></p>
</div>
